The paper deals with the impact of in-band full-duplex (IBFD) wireless communications on secret key generation via physical layer channel state information. This involves the study of wireless channels, information theory, and network security, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the proposed key generation strategy involves the use of multipath fading channels, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the overhead imposed by the self-interference channel estimation phase, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
